@NODE "rev" "History"
@TOC "MAIN"
                       Revision history (very brief).
                      -------------------------------- 
    First version.  (never released to the public)
  CLI-based version. I simply opened a console window and read all
  commands from the keyboard. Extremely boring.

    Number two.     (never released to the public)
  Opened a 'real' intuition window, wherefrom the commands where taken.
  You clicked the number you wished to move and the progress was shown
  in a console window.

    Third attempt.  (first release)
  For the first time the actual progress was shown at the same place as
  you gave your orders. For the first time the game became playable ;-)

    Current version (v3.3).
  I'm rather satisfied with this one, actually. I think the GUI looks
  quite nice and I've tested everything I can think of and I haven't
  found any remaining bugs. (Please report if you find any.)

    @{"Future versions." LINK "future"}
  
